The vulnerability (CVE-2015-8839) involves improper synchronization when handling the page cache and inode's mapping structure, leading to race conditions and potential data corruption. The solution behavior recommended is to use proper locking mechanisms, specifically acquiring a write lock on the inode's mapping semaphore before modifying the page cache and ensuring the lock is released properly.

